{
  "guid": "nsgt",
  "name": "Noise gate",
  "description": "This algorithm is a multi-channel noise gate. Each channel is fully independent – this being a multichannel algorithm is simply a convenience so that if you want a noise gate on all 12 module inputs, you don’t need to add 12 copies of the algorithm to do so.\n\nA sidechain input is available, to gate one signal with another.\n\nThe algorithm always works as an insert effect i.e. the output replaces the input.",
  "categories": [
    "Dynamics",
    "Audio Processing",
    "Multi-channel"
  ],
  "short_description": "A simple noise gate",
